                <note rend="inline" type="source">314.115C43/22: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-19T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 19, 1928—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>44. Department informed that Percy W. Shufeldt of Belize, British Honduras, has a
                    concession which he has been operating for some years for the exploitation of
                    chicle in Guatemala and that bill is now before Guatemalan Congress to cancel
                    the concession. Please investigate and report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
